reviews.review_text: Thanks Mr.Miller for another killer clean up! Must have been three inches of rain in the parking lot that night. Just nasty wet and cold...First night of a good solid four night run. Well, as solid as can be  I suppose for 91. If memory serves Jerry walked from the left side of the stage to the right before tuning up...never saw him do this before, and his slow walk across the Oakland Coliseum stage still makes me smile. Of course this could have been me just tripping my face off...as the liquid in Oakland was always great for these New Years runs. The Terrapin is the stand out of the night with a surprise smoker of a MNS that really had the place dancing. Mexicali/Loose Lucy are forgettable. I have seen better shows, but this night has always stuck out for me as the conditions outside the coliseum were just plain nasty. West coast shows, maybe because the boys were close to home?, always had a certain exploratory patience to them. About half this shows really shines, as is the case with the latter years finding whole show gems is difficult.  The vibe on this night was slightly on the dark side.  Take care all and thank goodness archive is alive and kicking so that I can dance my bones around. Still am sad I could not see 200 more shows.

I was there... Went to this show with some buddies from high school. I was 19. I remember the rainy parking lot scene, and we got in a bit late (as Cold Rain and Snow was playing).

Remembered it was an average show with some good highlights. I remember my buddy Dave saying that every time he went to a Dead show they played Loose Lucy.

Anyway, I remember having a good time at the show. Always loved to see Mozart on guitar...After Halloween 1991, it seemed downhill from there.
